Interface AlgorithmManager

All Superinterfaces:
au.gov.ansto.bragg.base.common.All, Common, Control, Manage, au.gov.ansto.bragg.base.common.Publisher, Query, java.io.Serializable, Subscribe
All Known Implementing Classes:
AlgorithmManager_
public interface AlgorithmManager
extends Common, Manage, Control, Query, Subscribe

AlgorithmManager is the interface for cicada algorithm manager application interface. This interface extends the other four interface of the algorithm manager, that is, Control, Manage, Query and Subscribe.

This interface integrated all the other four interfaces and add more abstract methods. User can use this interface to refer an algorithm manager object. Algorithm manager plays an key controller role in cicada project. It has the funtions of building an algorithm framework, loading source data and making the processors processing. It also has access to the status and result of all the processors. The run time life cycle of an algorithm manager object is the same as the cicada application.

This is the interface for developing user to creat and access everything of cicada.

void disposeData()
This method do the routine when the input signal is disposed. It will release the algorithm that was loaded on the signal.

getAvailableAlgorithmList

Algorithm[] getAvailableAlgorithmList()
Available algorithm is an algorithm structure loaded from a recipe file in the file system. This method will return an array that contains all the algorithm structures.

getCurrentAlgorithm

Algorithm getCurrentAlgorithm()
This method returns the algorithm handle of the algorithm manager. The current algorithm is loaded for a specific data signal. The algorithm manager can handle multiple data signal by putting them in a data signal list. When a data signal is loaded in to currentSignal member, the algorithm handle that applied to the data signal is also loaded into current algorithm. If a new algorithm is loaded upon the current data, the current algorithm handle is also updated to pointing to this algorithm.

Returns:
instance of Algorithm
See Also:
getAvailableAlgorithmList()
